1
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:43,960
There you go.

2
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:45,440
A hundred and fifty.

3
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:47,759
Nice job.

4
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:49,960
Go ahead, scan it.

5
00:01:57,600 --> 00:01:58,360
You crazy or something?

6
00:01:58,600 --> 00:01:59,360
I'll pay you

7
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:00,440
to talk Qing Ye

8
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:01,760
into going abroad.

9
00:02:05,440 --> 00:02:06,760
If you've got money to burn,

10
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:08,120
go sponsor some poor kids.

11
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:14,640
Quite a temper.

12
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,840
Nobody ever does something for someone

13
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:33,600
for no reason,

14
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:34,640
or expects nothing back.

15
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:36,760
If someone's willing to be good to you,

16
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:37,760
there's always a reason.

17
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:53,640
Hey, Kyle.

18
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:56,360
You asleep? Come out.

19
00:02:58,160 --> 00:02:58,840
[Nah, nah.]

20
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:00,520
[Got work tomorrow, so I can't hang.]

21
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:01,800
[You get some sleep too, man.]

22
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:08,720
Hey, Big G.

23
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:09,960
You asleep?

24
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:11,320
Wanna come out?

25
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:14,240
[We're working with Kyle tomorrow.]

26
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:16,160
[Meet at four tomorrow morning.]

27
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:17,720
[Don't forget.]

28
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:56,040
Nah.

29
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,480
It's barely past four.

30
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:01,480
What are you guys doing here?

31
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,440
It's already getting light out.

32
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:04,560
At this hour,

33
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:06,200
what are you doing in Wu's room?

34
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:08,280
Sleeping, of course.

35
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:11,960
Something came up last night.

36
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:14,440
Had nowhere to go, so I crashed here.

37
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:16,240
It's a party in here.

38
00:04:17,519 --> 00:04:19,279
You really have a thing for picking up strays, huh?

39
00:04:20,279 --> 00:04:21,320
A cousin is ok.

40
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,000
But what's this supposed to mean?

41
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:22,800
Your dad,

42
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,040
isn't he shorthanded for hauling?

43
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:25,640
Wanna be a grunt?

44
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:27,080
That wasn't on my schedule.

45
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,640
You don't get to crash at Xuan Island for free.

46
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:31,240
Didn't I already pay?

47
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,120
Around here,

48
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:34,040
money doesn't solve everything.

49
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,280
What's that smell?

50
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:48,080
It stinks.

51
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:50,560
Seafood.

52
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:51,560
Do you guys normally work

53
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,800
in this kind of environment?

54
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:54,360
No kidding.

55
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:55,560
It's just the four of us.

56
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:57,280
Aren't they people too?

57
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:00,000
Look at you.

58
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,120
If you can't handle it, don't force it.

59
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:02,880
Don't judge a book by its cover.

60
00:05:04,280 --> 00:05:05,080
Where do I change?

61
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:07,880
Go.

62
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:13,200
Ok.

63
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:15,760
Hey, be careful.

64
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:16,640
Don't worry.

65
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:26,520
Hey,

66
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:28,680
if you're gonna puke, go do it over there.

67
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:30,600
This is all seafood. You'll mess it up.

68
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,360
If you can't, don't push it.

69
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:38,960
I'm fine.

70
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:43,480
Okay.

71
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:44,640
Big G.

72
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:46,080
Catch this for me.

73
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:46,680
Sure.

74
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:54,920
If it's too much, just go back.

75
00:05:58,320 --> 00:05:59,000
I'm fine.

76
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:00,640
I'm used to having seafood

77
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:01,280
in a restaurant.

78
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:03,200
This is my first time getting up close.

79
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:03,920
It's a little overwhelming.

80
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:05,560
Alright, listen.

81
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:08,040
Go load the truck over there.

82
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:09,320
The smell's not as bad over there.

83
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:10,560
Got it.

84
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:18,080
Xing Wu?

85
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:21,600
Ye.

86
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:23,440
Where are you going?

87
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:24,360
Going for a run.

88
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:25,800
Sit down.

89
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:26,920
Let me talk to you for a sec.

90
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:30,920
Auntie.

91
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,600
This mask really fits your face shape.

92
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:34,400
Really?

93
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:37,040
This is the one you gave me.

94
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:38,240
What's it called?

95
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,040
Clinique.

96
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:41,040
Right.

97
00:06:41,159 --> 00:06:42,120
Whatever it is.

98
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:43,720
So yesterday,

99
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:45,120
I heard you tell me

100
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,440
that Meng wants to take you abroad.

101
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:48,960
I didn't sleep a wink

102
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:50,920
all night.

103
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:52,480
I mean, as your aunt,

104
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:53,880
I gotta have a real talk with you.

105
00:06:56,159 --> 00:06:57,560
This thing about going abroad with Meng,

106
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:59,880
you really need to think it over.

107
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:02,400
Sometimes, you get a hand of cards,

108
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:03,600
and you think

109
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,720
you're gonna score big?

110
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:06,000
But then by the end,

111
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:07,200
you end up losing big.

112
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:08,520
You get what I'm saying?

113
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:11,640
Mahjong really is a national treasure.

114
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:13,480
So full of life lessons.

115
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:15,640
Look, I've been there before.

116
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:16,600
Made my share of mistakes.

117
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:18,240
I don't want you to fall into the same traps.

118
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:19,240
When it comes to people,

119
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:20,960
you gotta keep your eyes open.

120
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:22,680
Especially with men.

121
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:24,160
You can't just get all hot-headed

122
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:25,920
and run off with someone.

123
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:28,000
Auntie, where is this coming from?

124
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,080
It's not running off.

125
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:31,400
He's taking me abroad to study.

126
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:32,480
Going abroad to study?

127
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:34,240
Isn't that just running off?

128
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:35,560
That's even worse.

129
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:36,440
I checked

130
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:38,000
all those interview invitations,

131
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,159
financial proof and everything.

132
00:07:39,159 --> 00:07:39,880
They're all real.

133
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:41,960
What do his parents think?

134
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,600
Back then,

135
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:45,400
didn't Wu also make the call on his own

136
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:46,560
to bring me back from Beijing?

137
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:47,440
Didn't he tell you?

138
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,240
Can you even compare him to Wu?

139
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:51,000
Wu is my son.

140
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:52,680
I raised him.

141
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:53,920
His character is solid.

142
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:55,520
Anyway,

143
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,560
before he gets my okay,

144
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,560
you can't just run off with him

145
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,680
without really knowing

146
00:07:58,680 --> 00:07:59,440
what he's like.

147
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,160
Fine.

148
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,280
Whatever you say.

149
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:05,880
I'm going for my run now.

150
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:06,360
Okay.

151
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:10,440
See you when you get back!

152
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:13,120
Your steamed buns.

153
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:13,640
Thanks.

154
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:21,080
Thank you.

155
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:23,160
You've got nothing left in your stomach, huh?

156
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:24,400
Eat up.

157
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:32,960
This place really changes people.

158
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:34,600
Qing Ye's not the same

159
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:35,240
as before either.

160
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:37,320
How so?

161
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,039
Before,

162
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:40,799
she would've jumped at the chance

163
00:08:40,799 --> 00:08:41,960
to go abroad.

164
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:44,360
Not waste time here

165
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:45,640
propping up a barbershop.

166
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:48,840
I asked her that too.

167
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:50,840
She doesn't think it's a waste.

168
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:56,040
Sure, the environment can change a person.

169
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:57,560
But Qing Ye

170
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,560
also has the power to change it back.

171
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:01,760
Morning, Ye.

172
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:02,240
Morning, Auntie.

173
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:03,160
Have you eaten?

174
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:04,520
Not yet. I'll eat when I get back.

175
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:05,240
Save me some, okay?

176
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:05,640
Sure.

177
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:06,440
Out for a run?

178
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:07,240
Morning, Uncle.

179
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:08,840
[Whatever she sets her mind to,]

180
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:09,600
Hope business is booming!

181
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,280
[she goes all in,]

182
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:11,200
[a hundred percent.]

183
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:12,440
Such a sweet talker.

184
00:09:14,040 --> 00:09:14,600
Hey, Bo.

185
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,240
You should go for a run too.

186
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:17,280
Lose some weight, eat a little less.

187
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:18,320
[Before you know it,]

188
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,200
[she draws you in,]

189
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:20,480
[and you just go along with her.]

190
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:21,080
Granny Zhang,

191
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:23,360
these eggplants look really good.

192
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:25,680
Come pick some when they're ripe.

193
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:27,080
Going for a run.

194
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:28,320
Through her light,

195
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,560
you see who you really are.

196
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:34,840
Look, I admit,

197
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:37,000
she's having fun

198
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:37,960
here.

199
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:39,760
But this is just

200
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:40,840
a little vacation kick for her.

201
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:43,840
She belongs to a much bigger world.

202
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:45,840
If you really care about her,

203
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:47,360
help me convince her

204
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:48,240
to come abroad with me.

205
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:51,920
I'm not her.

206
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,440
I can't just push my own perspective

207
00:09:54,640 --> 00:09:55,520
and interfere with her choices.

208
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:00,440
What if I told you

209
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:02,400
that what I'm offering

210
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:03,720
is exactly the life she wants?

211
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:13,320
Look.

212
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:16,920
[Happy birthday to you.]

213
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:20,320
[Happy birthday to you.]

214
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:21,520
[Make a wish.]

215
00:10:21,560 --> 00:10:22,240
[Okay! Okay! I'm making it.]

216
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:24,880
[When I turn twenty,]

217
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,320
[I'm gonna be]

218
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,680
[at a top ten school in the world,]

219
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:29,120
[studying business.]

220
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:31,560
[And I'm gonna travel the world too.]

221
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:34,040
[I wanna go to Egypt to see the pyramids,]

222
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,640
[go to Pompeii,]

223
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:36,880
[and also to Chile]

224
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:38,840
[to watch a volcano erupt live.]

225
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:40,920
[Anyway,]

226
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,400
[as long as I want it,]

227
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,640
[the world is at my feet.]

228
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:48,480
This is who she should be.

229
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:51,400
This place is just

230
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,520
a temporary safe harbor for her.

231
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:54,360
Now the wind's picking up.

232
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:56,360
You need to help her set sail again.

233
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:03,360
Why do you think

234
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:04,320
I can talk her into it?

235
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:08,160
Whether you can or not is one thing,

236
00:11:08,560 --> 00:11:10,120
but your trying is better than not trying.

237
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:15,120
Xing Wu!

238
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:18,040
Xing Wu!

239
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:31,280
[As long as I want it,]

240
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:33,480
[the world is at my feet.]

241
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:57,640
How come you two are together?

242
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:01,120
It's a long story.

243
00:12:03,880 --> 00:12:04,480
Take the fish back.

244
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:06,000
Use it to butter up my mom.

245
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:07,080
You can't stay at my place for free.

246
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:08,920
Fine.

247
00:12:09,280 --> 00:12:10,800
Think about what I said, okay?

248
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:12,600
What'd you say?

249
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:14,680
Guy stuff.

250
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:15,920
I'm out.

251
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:19,880
Did you eat?

252
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:26,920
What kind of hairstyle are we doing today?

253
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,680
Give me a perm like this.

254
00:12:30,560 --> 00:12:31,160
Is her hairstyle

255
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:32,280
the hottest one right now?

256
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:33,600
Yeah.

257
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:34,960
Then give me that.

258
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:35,720
Got it.

259
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:38,240
Liu Nian's the best at it.

260
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:40,160
He'll do a great perm for you.

261
00:12:40,560 --> 00:12:41,640
Okay, I promise you'll love it.

262
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,240
Boss lady, can you give me a discount?

263
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:44,560
Twenty percent off.

264
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,320
You're so generous!

265
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:49,000
Take good care of her, alright?

266
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:49,520
You got it.

267
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:52,640
Auntie.

268
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:57,520
Call me Aunt.

269
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:00,080
Aunt.

270
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:02,120
I was working at the dock this morning,

271
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:03,000
and I brought you a fish.

272
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:04,600
Working, huh?

273
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:07,080
Okay.

274
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:08,880
Now you're starting to feel like a local.

275
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:12,720
I was just looking for you.

276
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:14,160
And here you come.

277
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:16,160
Give me the fish.

278
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:21,720
You're an adult, right?

279
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:27,680
Aunt,

280
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:29,000
what are you...

281
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:31,760
Yesterday,

282
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:33,120
your cake was so sweet.

283
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:34,160
It completely clouded my judgment.

284
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:36,880
I didn't realize

285
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:37,840
you were after Ye.

286
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:40,200
No, you've got it wrong.

287
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,560
Ye and I are just friends.

288
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:43,240
I only came to help her.

289
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:45,000
You city kids,

290
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,240
so smooth

291
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:47,200
with your words.

292
00:13:47,880 --> 00:13:49,280
I can't outtalk you.

293
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:51,440
But today,

294
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:52,720
I asked you to sit here

295
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:54,280
just to test you.

296
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:56,440
To see how much you can handle.

297
00:13:57,040 --> 00:13:57,600
Alright.

298
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:58,520
Aunt.

299
00:13:58,800 --> 00:13:59,680
How do you want to test me?

300
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:03,080
We have a saying

301
00:14:03,160 --> 00:14:04,280
here.

302
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:05,680
A man's courage

303
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:07,240
is as big as

304
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:08,920
his tolerance for alcohol.

305
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:13,840
Okay.

306
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:14,920
Aunt,

307
00:14:15,080 --> 00:14:16,080
I've always been brave,

308
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:17,680
ever since I was a kid.

309
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:18,480
Here goes.

310
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:26,960
Not bad, kid.

311
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,920
Not bad.

312
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:38,720
Come on,

313
00:14:39,160 --> 00:14:40,240
let's keep drinking then.

314
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:45,080
Meng!

315
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:47,280
Are you okay?

316
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:50,480
Wake up.

317
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,280
What a brave guy.

318
00:15:20,040 --> 00:15:21,440
Meng Ruihang wants me to talk you into

319
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:23,360
going abroad with him.

320
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:28,800
Well, he picked the wrong person.

321
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:30,920
You said

322
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:32,720
you wouldn't interfere.

323
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:37,200
Not necessarily.

324
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:40,000
You want me to go with him?

325
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:48,880
I think

326
00:15:50,160 --> 00:15:51,440
it'd be good for you to go.

327
00:15:58,240 --> 00:15:58,760
Why?

328
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:06,080
Do you know the difference

329
00:16:07,160 --> 00:16:08,800
between migratory birds and resident birds?

330
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:12,360
What are you trying to say?

331
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:18,200
Resident birds don't migrate with the seasons.

332
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:20,800
They're born and raised in one place.

333
00:16:22,520 --> 00:16:23,400
But migratory birds are different.

334
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:26,320
Every winter,

335
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:27,960
swans from Siberia

336
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:28,760
fly here

337
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:30,080
to spend the winter.

338
00:16:31,360 --> 00:16:32,280
Then when it warms up,

339
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:33,480
and spring comes,

340
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:35,160
they fly back

341
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:36,160
to their original home.

342
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:39,680
So you think I'm a migratory bird?

343
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:46,000
You should go back to your normal life.

344
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:48,200
This place isn't right for you.

345
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:51,560
And it's not worth staying for.

346
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:57,080
Whether it's worth it or not,

347
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:58,760
I'll decide for myself.

348
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:01,360
Don't forget your promise.

349
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:03,160
If I leave,

350
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:05,720
make sure you come see me off.

351
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:15,800
It's a deal.

352
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:18,920
Okay.

353
00:17:37,720 --> 00:17:39,240
He's way too heavy.

354
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:40,600
Hey, you.

355
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:42,360
Lanfang, let's put him down here for a bit.

356
00:17:42,360 --> 00:17:43,080
I can't carry him anymore.

357
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:44,720
Alright, alright, come on.

358
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:46,920
Easy.

359
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:51,480
This kid.

360
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:53,880
Looked pretty tough,

361
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:55,120
but turns out he can't hold his liquor at all.

362
00:17:56,560 --> 00:17:57,520
Needs more practice.

363
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:01,120
What's wrong with him?

364
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:02,800
Drank too much.

365
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:04,480
Drank too much?

366
00:18:05,280 --> 00:18:06,840
Who'd he drink with, this early?

367
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:09,840
Just one bottle.

368
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:10,640
Actually,

369
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:12,920
I just wanted to test how much he could drink.

370
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:16,840
Didn't expect him to be so reckless.

371
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:18,880
He thought he could hold his liquor, but he couldn't.

372
00:18:19,440 --> 00:18:21,040
Still, you can tell

373
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:23,360
he really cares about you.

374
00:18:25,280 --> 00:18:26,680
But this recklessness of his,

375
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:28,680
he's really not as good as our Wu.

376
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:29,840
I mean, our Wu,

377
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:30,840
isn't he

378
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:33,000
steady, reliable, and level-headed?

379
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:34,920
Anyway,

380
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:37,440
about going abroad,

381
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:38,440
I think you should

382
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:39,600
think it over some more.

383
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:41,880
Don't worry, Auntie.

384
00:18:41,960 --> 00:18:42,840
I know what I'm doing.

385
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:45,120
Qing Ye.

386
00:18:46,560 --> 00:18:47,360
I'm gonna take you with me.

387
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:49,520
I swear. I'm gonna take you.

388
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:51,840
So devoted.

389
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:55,120
I can still drink.

390
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:55,840
What are you drinking for?

391
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:56,480
Come on, hurry.

392
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:57,800
I can't carry him anymore.

393
00:18:58,120 --> 00:18:58,760
Quick.

394
00:18:58,760 --> 00:18:59,920
People are passing by.

395
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,360
What if a customer comes?

396
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:01,840
Wait.

397
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:03,720
Put him on Wu's bed.

398
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:05,200
Give me a hand.

399
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:06,120
Come on.

400
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:07,600
Come on.

401
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:22,480
I can still drink.

402
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:23,800
No more for you.

403
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:26,960
I'll get him some water.

404
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:51,360
Can I come in?

405
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:52,880
Hold on.

406
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:53,720
I'm coming out.

407
00:19:58,440 --> 00:19:59,680
What's up?

408
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:40,600
Hello?

409
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:41,560
Who's this?

410
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:44,960
[Did Meng Ruihang come looking for you?]

411
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:48,440
I don't have to answer that.

412
00:20:50,920 --> 00:20:52,000
[Do you know he fell out with his parents]

413
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,480
[because of you?]

414
00:22:07,320 --> 00:22:09,320
Slacking off at work?

415
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:11,920
Not really your style,

416
00:22:11,920 --> 00:22:13,080
Mr. Workaholic.

417
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:14,200
What's up?

418
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:15,920
Just been sitting too long.

419
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:16,880
Need to get up and move around.

420
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,440
You've been working hard.

421
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:21,160
I brought you some food.

422
00:22:23,120 --> 00:22:23,680
Thanks.

423
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:27,360
There's a high wind warning for tonight.

424
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:29,080
It's too dangerous. You shouldn't go back.

425
00:22:29,160 --> 00:22:30,080
Just stay here.

426
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:33,120
Alright, fine.

427
00:22:36,360 --> 00:22:37,000
Well,

428
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:38,720
I heard

429
00:22:39,640 --> 00:22:41,120
that childhood friend of Qing Ye's,

430
00:22:41,480 --> 00:22:42,440
he's trying to take her abroad.

431
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:46,880
For real?

432
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:56,480
She was always gonna go abroad.

433
00:22:57,320 --> 00:22:57,920
She's just going back

434
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:58,920
to her original plan.

435
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:21,560
Better she leaves

436
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:22,840
before she gets too attached to this place.

437
00:23:46,320 --> 00:23:46,880
Qing Ye.

438
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:48,520
Qing Ye.

439
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:07,680
Where is she?

440
00:24:09,760 --> 00:24:10,360
She left.

441
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:11,600
Left?

442
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:13,880
How could she just leave

443
00:24:13,880 --> 00:24:14,880
without saying anything?

444
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:16,200
With that guy Meng?

445
00:24:18,880 --> 00:24:19,160
Honestly,

446
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:20,360
I'm still kind of worried

447
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:21,720
about her being with him.

448
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:23,040
I mean, they're just two high schoolers.

449
00:24:23,320 --> 00:24:24,720
What if something happens?

450
00:24:28,360 --> 00:24:30,040
You should go back to your normal life.

451
00:24:31,040 --> 00:24:32,040
This place isn't right for you.

452
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:34,280
And it's not worth staying for.

453
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:36,920
Whether it's worth it or not,

454
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:38,560
I'll decide for myself.

455
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:41,640
Don't forget your promise.

456
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:44,880
If I leave,

457
00:24:46,440 --> 00:24:47,320
make sure you come see me off.

458
00:24:51,120 --> 00:24:51,680
Wu.

459
00:24:56,640 --> 00:24:57,760
Oh, girl.

460
00:25:14,840 --> 00:25:15,920
You know what this is?

461
00:25:19,880 --> 00:25:20,520
Wheat.

462
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:23,480
Not wheat.

463
00:25:24,560 --> 00:25:25,480
It's barnyard grass.

464
00:25:26,240 --> 00:25:27,680
A weed that grows in rice fields.

465
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:30,760
So what's the difference?

466
00:25:31,360 --> 00:25:31,880
Qing Ye,

467
00:25:32,200 --> 00:25:33,040
you don't need to know

468
00:25:33,040 --> 00:25:34,360
the difference between them.

469
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:35,520
You don't need to know how fishermen

470
00:25:35,520 --> 00:25:36,800
go out and fish.

471
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:38,480
And you definitely don't need to haul fish.

472
00:25:39,160 --> 00:25:40,600
You were never meant to be here.

473
00:25:41,360 --> 00:25:42,240
Let's go back to Beijing together.

474
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:43,440
We can live better there.

475
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:47,280
Will we really?

476
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:53,760
Actually,

477
00:25:54,280 --> 00:25:55,040
once you know something,

478
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:57,200
you can't act like you don't.

479
00:25:58,520 --> 00:25:59,360
Like me,

480
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:02,040
I know how much it hurts to lose family.

481
00:26:02,880 --> 00:26:04,720
So I can't just stand there

482
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:05,840
and watch you

483
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:07,040
break away from your family

484
00:26:07,520 --> 00:26:08,720
and still accept your kindness.

485
00:26:09,600 --> 00:26:11,320
So you know everything.

486
00:26:12,600 --> 00:26:13,720
He Leling told me.

487
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:15,200
She said you had a huge fight with your parents

488
00:26:15,200 --> 00:26:15,920
and ran away.

489
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:17,520
Qing Ye,

490
00:26:17,520 --> 00:26:19,000
I can fix this.

491
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:20,040
I know.

492
00:26:21,440 --> 00:26:22,000
Yes,

493
00:26:22,480 --> 00:26:23,680
if I go abroad with you,

494
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:25,920
maybe it would really start

495
00:26:25,920 --> 00:26:27,000
a whole new life.

496
00:26:27,880 --> 00:26:28,920
But I don't want that.

497
00:26:29,280 --> 00:26:30,680
I still want to make it on my own.

498
00:26:30,680 --> 00:26:31,600
Fight my own battles

499
00:26:31,880 --> 00:26:33,440
and live the life I want.

500
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:39,200
Just like someone once told me,

501
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:43,480
You can still be the same as before.

502
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:45,320
Don't lean on anyone else.

503
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:47,160
Live proud.

504
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:52,200
Bus is coming.

505
00:26:53,040 --> 00:26:54,440
When you get to the county town,

506
00:26:54,520 --> 00:26:56,040
just take a taxi to the station.

507
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:01,720
Who knows when

508
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:03,480
we'll see each other again.

509
00:27:06,280 --> 00:27:07,480
Text me when you get home.

510
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:11,280
Still, I'm really worried about you.

511
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:12,200
Don't be.

512
00:27:13,640 --> 00:27:15,040
I can take care of myself. Anywhere.

513
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:17,720
Next time,

514
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:19,200
we'll both be

515
00:27:19,520 --> 00:27:21,000
better than we are now.

516
00:27:29,840 --> 00:27:30,400
Goodbye.

517
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:31,400
See you.

518
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:38,800
Qing Ye,

519
00:27:39,480 --> 00:27:40,360
anytime you need me,

520
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:42,120
just call and I'll come.

521
00:28:46,160 --> 00:28:46,920
You didn't leave?

522
00:28:48,840 --> 00:28:49,520
Where would I go?

523
00:28:58,960 --> 00:28:59,920
So, are you still coming home with me?

524
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:02,640
Yeah, of course.

525
00:29:06,560 --> 00:29:07,880
But before we go home,

526
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:10,040
you have to take me somewhere first.

527
00:29:11,760 --> 00:29:12,400
Where?

528
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:22,760
You wouldn't tell me the whole way here.

529
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:24,040
What's with the mattress?

530
00:29:25,600 --> 00:29:26,160
You can't keep

531
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:27,360
sleeping on cardboard.

532
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:28,480
It's bad for your back.

533
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:29,960
And I'd feel awful.

534
00:29:31,560 --> 00:29:32,720
Where'd you get the money for a mattress?

535
00:29:34,320 --> 00:29:35,680
I sold some of my clothes online.

536
00:29:35,920 --> 00:29:37,000
Got a pretty good price, actually.

537
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:38,360
Look.

538
00:29:40,520 --> 00:29:42,200
The only thing is, it's a pain to ship from Zhazhating.

539
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:44,080
So I went all the way to the county town to mail them.

540
00:29:44,320 --> 00:29:45,600
You brought those all the way from Beijing,

541
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:46,440
and now you're just selling them?

542
00:29:48,840 --> 00:29:50,200
Look, clothes don't matter.

543
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:51,880
What matters is you getting a good night's sleep

544
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:52,720
after working hard all day.

545
00:29:53,280 --> 00:29:54,600
Besides, school starts soon.

546
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:55,440
Everyone wears uniforms.

547
00:29:55,680 --> 00:29:56,440
I wouldn't even get to wear them.

548
00:30:00,440 --> 00:30:01,040
Thanks.

549
00:30:04,840 --> 00:30:05,840
But I'm curious though.

550
00:30:06,800 --> 00:30:08,440
Who's the big spender?

551
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:11,160
The site protects people's privacy.

552
00:30:11,360 --> 00:30:12,040
How would I know?

553
00:30:12,040 --> 00:30:12,880
Can't even look it up.

554
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:14,560
Don't worry.

555
00:30:14,680 --> 00:30:15,840
Those clothes were pretty much new.

556
00:30:15,840 --> 00:30:16,680
I sold them super cheap.

557
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:17,440
They got a good deal.

558
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:19,200
I got rid of stuff I don't use.

559
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:21,160
You get better sleep.

560
00:30:21,560 --> 00:30:22,040
Triple win.

561
00:30:24,360 --> 00:30:24,920
Alright, fine.

562
00:30:44,080 --> 00:30:45,240
This mattress is pretty big.

563
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:50,720
Not going on that trip with Shu Han,

564
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:52,480
do you regret it?

565
00:30:56,240 --> 00:30:56,880
No.

566
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:01,560
Right.

567
00:31:02,120 --> 00:31:03,360
You never wanted to go anyway.

568
00:31:07,120 --> 00:31:07,720
What about you?

569
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:09,960
Do you regret staying here?

570
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:11,520
Yeah, I do.

571
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:18,920
But only for about a second.

572
00:31:25,360 --> 00:31:26,880
So why didn't you go with Meng Ruihang?

573
00:31:27,680 --> 00:31:29,080
Because that's not what I wanted.

574
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:36,160
Lie down and try it.

575
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:39,080
This mattress is not just big, it's soft.

576
00:31:39,240 --> 00:31:39,840
Really comfortable.

577
00:31:40,040 --> 00:31:41,120
Go on, try it.

578
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:52,240
How is it?

579
00:31:54,800 --> 00:31:55,560
I've never

580
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:57,040
lain down in a car like this before.

581
00:31:58,080 --> 00:31:58,880
It's actually pretty nice.

582
00:32:01,680 --> 00:32:02,640
You know,

583
00:32:03,520 --> 00:32:05,640
all that stuff in Zhazhating,

584
00:32:07,280 --> 00:32:08,840
I never would've imagined any of it.

585
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:12,160
It was all so exciting

586
00:32:12,760 --> 00:32:13,520
and unforgettable.

587
00:32:18,520 --> 00:32:19,480
So now,

588
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:21,680
I don't want to leave this place.

589
00:32:27,680 --> 00:32:28,280
Qing Ye,

590
00:32:31,520 --> 00:32:32,680
you stay here.

591
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:34,960
I won't let you regret it.

592
00:32:38,840 --> 00:32:39,640
What did you say?

593
00:32:51,560 --> 00:32:52,160
I said,

594
00:32:55,480 --> 00:32:56,720
if you stay here too long,

595
00:32:58,800 --> 00:32:59,840
you will regret it.

596
00:34:13,440 --> 00:34:14,800
Are they coming back?

597
00:34:15,199 --> 00:34:16,040
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

598
00:34:16,239 --> 00:34:17,560
Wu just called

599
00:34:17,560 --> 00:34:18,719
and said they're already on their way.

600
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:32,840
Grandma.

601
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:33,440
Wu! Wu!

602
00:34:33,719 --> 00:34:34,440
Where's Ye?

603
00:34:36,320 --> 00:34:36,880
Grandma.

604
00:34:38,600 --> 00:34:39,120
You are. You are.

605
00:34:39,120 --> 00:34:40,040
Grandma. Auntie.

606
00:34:40,040 --> 00:34:40,760
Come here, give me a hug.

607
00:34:41,480 --> 00:34:43,520
Why are you all waiting outside?

608
00:34:43,639 --> 00:34:46,040
We were waiting for you to come back.

609
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:46,639
Yeah.

610
00:34:46,639 --> 00:34:47,800
Wu called earlier

611
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:49,000
and said you didn't leave.

612
00:34:49,239 --> 00:34:50,320
So we just figured

613
00:34:50,320 --> 00:34:52,040
we'd wait for you out here.

614
00:34:52,159 --> 00:34:53,440
Wait for you to come home for dinner.

615
00:34:54,199 --> 00:34:55,159
See? I told you.

616
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:57,600
Ye never wanted to leave.

617
00:34:58,480 --> 00:34:59,520
Grandma knows me best.

618
00:35:01,160 --> 00:35:03,200
You scared me to death.

619
00:35:03,240 --> 00:35:04,360
You took that welwitschia

620
00:35:04,360 --> 00:35:05,120
with you.

621
00:35:05,120 --> 00:35:06,520
I really thought you were gone.

622
00:35:06,520 --> 00:35:07,120
No.

623
00:35:07,160 --> 00:35:08,680
That plant is in my room.

624
00:35:08,680 --> 00:35:09,360
You have it?

625
00:35:09,360 --> 00:35:10,960
I didn't even know what that plant was.

626
00:35:10,960 --> 00:35:12,360
So she showed it to me.

627
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:13,440
Oh, I see.

628
00:35:14,360 --> 00:35:15,480
If I were really leaving,

629
00:35:15,480 --> 00:35:17,040
of course I'd tell you first.

630
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:18,160
Besides,

631
00:35:18,440 --> 00:35:19,240
I don't want to leave anyway.

632
00:35:23,680 --> 00:35:25,240
Alright. Alright.

633
00:35:26,200 --> 00:35:26,480
Wait.

634
00:35:26,480 --> 00:35:26,920
How did you

635
00:35:26,920 --> 00:35:27,920
come back in this truck?

636
00:35:27,920 --> 00:35:28,320
Right.

637
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:29,120
There's stuff in the truck.

638
00:35:29,440 --> 00:35:29,840
Yeah.

639
00:35:29,960 --> 00:35:30,520
Liu Nian.

640
00:35:31,200 --> 00:35:31,720
Coming!

641
00:35:31,720 --> 00:35:32,280
Come help.

642
00:35:32,840 --> 00:35:33,360
Easy, easy.

643
00:35:33,360 --> 00:35:33,680
Okay.

644
00:35:34,320 --> 00:35:35,560
Here, you take the back.

645
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:36,000
Got it.

646
00:35:36,680 --> 00:35:37,520
Why'd you buy

647
00:35:37,520 --> 00:35:38,720
a mattress?

648
00:35:39,040 --> 00:35:40,120
Qing Ye bought it for me.

649
00:35:40,600 --> 00:35:41,120
She insisted.

650
00:35:42,960 --> 00:35:43,880
Mom, you gotta tell her.

651
00:35:46,920 --> 00:35:47,440
Okay, okay.

652
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:49,080
I insisted.

653
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:50,160
I spent too much.

654
00:35:50,320 --> 00:35:50,920
Go ahead.

655
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:55,320
Good buy.

656
00:35:57,960 --> 00:35:59,880
This is from Cici.

657
00:35:59,880 --> 00:36:01,120
Their family just pickled it fresh.

658
00:36:01,480 --> 00:36:02,000
And this is

659
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:03,640
Zhao Pock's chicken.

660
00:36:03,880 --> 00:36:05,600
And these two dishes, I made them.

661
00:36:05,880 --> 00:36:07,240
Come on, eat up, eat up.

662
00:36:07,520 --> 00:36:08,440
Let me try yours first.

663
00:36:08,560 --> 00:36:09,600
Same here.

664
00:36:09,600 --> 00:36:10,520
I have a feeling mine

665
00:36:10,520 --> 00:36:11,680
tastes pretty good too.

666
00:36:11,800 --> 00:36:12,280
Mmm.

667
00:36:12,640 --> 00:36:14,000
Here, Ye, have some chicken.

668
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:14,440
Mmm.

669
00:36:14,440 --> 00:36:15,440
So good.

670
00:36:16,760 --> 00:36:17,640
You know what?

671
00:36:17,720 --> 00:36:18,720
Liunian and I were slammed

672
00:36:18,720 --> 00:36:19,920
from morning till night today.

673
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:21,200
We're gonna pay off the debt

674
00:36:21,200 --> 00:36:22,280
really soon.

675
00:36:22,800 --> 00:36:23,680
No kidding? That's awesome.

676
00:36:23,760 --> 00:36:24,440
I mean it.

677
00:36:24,640 --> 00:36:25,240
Trust me.

678
00:36:25,640 --> 00:36:26,320
We do.

679
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:28,040
All of us.

680
00:36:38,400 --> 00:36:39,200
The wardrobe.

681
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:42,120
So you built it for me.

682
00:36:43,080 --> 00:36:44,600
Yeah. Too bad, though.

683
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:45,480
Your clothes

684
00:36:45,480 --> 00:36:46,840
all got sold online.

685
00:36:47,120 --> 00:36:48,000
There aren't many left.

686
00:36:48,680 --> 00:36:49,440
No big deal.

687
00:36:49,960 --> 00:36:51,600
If it can't hold clothes, I'll put books in it.

688
00:36:51,920 --> 00:36:52,440
Okay.

689
00:36:52,920 --> 00:36:54,040
Whatever you want. It's built already.

690
00:36:54,360 --> 00:36:55,200
You can put anything in there.

691
00:36:56,280 --> 00:36:57,720
School's about to start.

692
00:36:57,960 --> 00:36:58,920
I'm gonna work hard

693
00:36:59,280 --> 00:37:02,200
and try to be the top student in Zhazhating.

694
00:37:02,960 --> 00:37:03,880
I think you can do it.

695
00:37:04,280 --> 00:37:05,120
I think so too.

696
00:37:50,720 --> 00:37:51,440
Qing Ye,

697
00:37:53,080 --> 00:37:54,320
you stay here.

698
00:37:55,360 --> 00:37:56,560
I won't let you regret it.

699
00:38:58,360 --> 00:38:58,880
How is it?

700
00:38:59,080 --> 00:38:59,560
Are you happy?

701
00:39:00,600 --> 00:39:01,640
Of course I am.

702
00:39:01,800 --> 00:39:03,040
Haven't been to an amusement park in ages.

703
00:39:03,480 --> 00:39:05,240
Gotta relax a bit before school starts.

704
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:05,720
Great.

705
00:39:06,480 --> 00:39:06,960
Let's go.

706
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:46,920
This is good.

707
00:39:53,200 --> 00:39:53,800
What are you laughing at?

708
00:39:53,800 --> 00:39:54,360
Hold on.

709
00:39:55,160 --> 00:39:55,960
Let me take a picture of you.

710
00:39:58,480 --> 00:39:59,040
See?

711
00:40:00,600 --> 00:40:01,560
You're so bad.

712
00:40:26,840 --> 00:40:27,520
Xing Wu.

713
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:31,280
Look.

714
00:40:31,320 --> 00:40:31,800
What's up?

715
00:40:32,520 --> 00:40:34,120
A teacher from Anzi County No. 1 High School

716
00:40:34,120 --> 00:40:35,080
just messaged me.

717
00:40:35,440 --> 00:40:37,040
They've finished my enrollment paperwork.

718
00:40:37,200 --> 00:40:38,240
And they want me to go register next week.

719
00:40:39,040 --> 00:40:39,560
That's great.

720
00:40:40,280 --> 00:40:41,160
Do you know that school?

721
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:43,480
What do you think?

722
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:47,000
I know it like the back of my hand.

723
00:40:47,920 --> 00:40:48,680
When you go register,

724
00:40:48,680 --> 00:40:49,280
I'll take you there.

725
00:41:08,480 --> 00:41:09,440
Got everything ready?

726
00:41:13,040 --> 00:41:14,560
All the transfer documents are here.

727
00:41:16,160 --> 00:41:17,560
Mr. Sun sent them last week.

728
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:19,000
So we register today,

729
00:41:19,520 --> 00:41:20,480
and school starts next week.

730
00:41:21,040 --> 00:41:22,880
Then I'll officially be in class.

731
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:27,920
Qing Ye.

732
00:41:30,040 --> 00:41:30,640
Be honest.

733
00:41:31,800 --> 00:41:32,800
Do you regret staying here

734
00:41:33,560 --> 00:41:34,160
to go to school?

735
00:41:34,840 --> 00:41:35,360
No.

736
00:41:39,240 --> 00:41:40,920
This is the best choice

737
00:41:41,160 --> 00:41:42,280
I can make right now.

738
00:41:43,920 --> 00:41:45,120
Even if it's not perfect,

739
00:41:45,560 --> 00:41:46,160
I'll work hard

740
00:41:46,160 --> 00:41:47,280
to make it perfect.

741
00:41:51,160 --> 00:41:51,680
What?

742
00:41:52,600 --> 00:41:53,200
You don't believe me?

743
00:41:54,840 --> 00:41:55,360
No, I do.

744
00:41:57,560 --> 00:41:59,040
Come on, let's go to school.

745
00:42:19,360 --> 00:42:20,000
Stop here.

746
00:42:21,280 --> 00:42:22,600
You're pretty popular, huh?

747
00:42:23,040 --> 00:42:24,280
Even the security guard doesn't stop you.

748
00:42:25,080 --> 00:42:26,360
I fixed his phone a few times

749
00:42:26,680 --> 00:42:27,360
for free.

750
00:42:27,920 --> 00:42:28,720
So you just love fixing things

751
00:42:28,720 --> 00:42:29,760
for free?

752
00:42:30,640 --> 00:42:32,360
Same with the printer shop owner last time.

753
00:42:33,320 --> 00:42:34,200
Depends on my mood.

754
00:42:35,640 --> 00:42:36,720
Call it building good karma.

755
00:42:36,920 --> 00:42:38,360
Trading it for a friendly face at the gate isn't bad.

756
00:42:40,200 --> 00:42:40,920
This is the building.

757
00:42:41,160 --> 00:42:42,240
Third floor, turn right.

758
00:42:42,800 --> 00:42:43,680
I won't go in with you.

759
00:42:44,760 --> 00:42:45,280
Why not?

760
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:48,600
The guard doesn't stop me,

761
00:42:48,920 --> 00:42:49,520
but the teachers here

762
00:42:49,520 --> 00:42:50,440
aren't exactly happy to see me.

763
00:42:51,480 --> 00:42:52,200
I'll wait for you right here.

764
00:42:53,400 --> 00:42:54,400
Okay. I'm going.

765
00:43:10,360 --> 00:43:10,880
Come in.

766
00:43:13,640 --> 00:43:14,480
Hello, teacher.

767
00:43:14,920 --> 00:43:16,680
Here are my documents.

768
00:43:17,480 --> 00:43:18,720
Qing Ye, right?

769
00:43:18,960 --> 00:43:20,080
Come on in. Have a seat.

770
00:43:20,240 --> 00:43:20,680
Thank you.

771
00:43:20,720 --> 00:43:21,600
I've been expecting you.

772
00:43:26,440 --> 00:43:27,920
Here's your new uniform.

773
00:43:28,480 --> 00:43:29,440
Thank you, teacher.

774
00:43:29,680 --> 00:43:31,320
The school requires everyone to wear the uniform.

775
00:43:31,320 --> 00:43:32,000
This one's new.

776
00:43:32,640 --> 00:43:33,280
Please sign here.

777
00:43:33,440 --> 00:43:33,960
Okay.

778
00:43:40,440 --> 00:43:41,040
Can we have a chat?
